items.title: Blackmon first to reach 200 hits this season
items.summary: Charlie Blackmon's terrific season reached another milestone Tuesday. Blackmon roped a two-out, two-RBI double in the second inning for hit No. 200 of the season, becoming the first Rockies player to reach that plateau since Matt Holliday had 216 hits during the 2007 campaign.

items.title: Archer regains crispness after injury scare
items.summary: Chris Archer looked back to normal on Tuesday for the first time since returning from an injury scare in early September.
